In[33]:






data_gen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    rescale=1./255.,
    validation_split=0.2)

























Train_Test_Split


















In[34]:






train_generator = data_gen.flow_from_directory \
    (directory = base_directory,
    target_size=(image_size, image_size),
    class_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    shuffle=True,
    subset = 'training')

In[69]:






model = Sequential()





















In[70]:






model.add(Conv2D(filters = 32, kernel_size = (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape = (image_size,image_size,3)))
model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))





















In[71]:






model.add(Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))





















In[72]:






model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(classes, activation='softmax'))

In[83]:






def predict_class(image_path, model, target_size):
    # Load and preprocess the image
    img = Image.open(image_path)
    img = img.resize(target_size)
    img_array = np.array(img, dtype=np.float64)
    img_array = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)
    img_array /= 255.0  # Rescale pixel values to [0, 1]
    
    # Make prediction
    prediction = model.predict(img_array)
    
    # Print the prediction probabilities
    print("Prediction probabilities:", prediction[0])
    
    # Get the predicted class
    predicted_class = np.argmax(prediction)
    img = mpimg.imread(image_path)
    # Plot the image
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.axis('off')  # Turn off axis
    plt.show()
    # Print the predicted class
    print("Predicted class Number:", predicted_class)
    print("predicted_name :", class_indices[predicted_class] )
